<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Lesson: Work of Water</title>
    <script src="https://cdn.tailwindcss.com"></script>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Crimson+Pro:ital,wght@0,400;0,700;1,400&family=Inter:wght@400;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <script src="https://unpkg.com/lucide@latest"></script>
    <style>
        body { font-family: 'Crimson Pro', serif; background: #fdfbf7; line-height: 1.7; }
        .page { background: white; max-width: 850px; margin: 40px auto; padding: 80px; box-shadow: 0 10px 30px rgba(0,0,0,0.05); border-radius: 32px; border: 1px solid #f1f5f9; }
        .action { font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-weight: 700; margin-top: 24px; color: #1e293b; font-size: 0.95rem; }
        .dialogue { margin-left: 40px; font-style: italic; color: #475569; position: relative; margin-bottom: 12px; }
        .dialogue::before { content: "—"; position: absolute; left: -20px; color: #cbd5e1; font-style: normal; }
        .illustrate { border: 2px dashed #e2e8f0; border-radius: 20px; margin: 35px 0; display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: center; justify-content: center; background: #fcfcfc; padding: 30px; }
        .illustrate-label { font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: 10px; font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.15em; color: #94a3b8; margin-top: 15px; }
        .material-box { background: #f8fafc; border-radius: 20px; border: 1px solid #e2e8f0; padding: 30px; margin-bottom: 40px; }
        .aside-box { background: #fffbeb; border-left: 4px solid #f59e0b; padding: 25px; margin: 40px 0; border-radius: 0 15px 15px 0; position: relative; }
        .aside-box::after { content: "Instructor's Aside"; position: absolute; top: -10px; left: 20px; background: #f59e0b; color: white; font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: 8px; font-weight: 900; padding: 2px 8px; border-radius: 4px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; }
        @media print { body { background: white; margin: 0; } .page { box-shadow: none; border: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; width: 100%; } .no-print { display: none; } }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="no-print p-6 flex justify-between items-center max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <a href="../../index.html" class="text-slate-400 font-bold uppercase text-[10px] tracking-widest flex items-center gap-2">
            <i data-lucide="arrow-left" size="14"></i> Back to Dashboard
        </a>
    </div>
    
    <article class="page">
        <header class="mb-12 border-b-2 border-amber-50 pb-8">
            <p class="font-sans font-bold text-amber-600 uppercase text-[10px] tracking-widest mb-2 italic">Geography // Work of Water</p>
            <h1 class="text-5xl font-bold text-slate-900 leading-tight">River Work: Carving, Carrying, Depositing</h1>
            <p class="mt-4 text-slate-400 italic">Guide: Elim Lee // AMI Elementary Submission</p>
        </header>

        <section class="material-box">
            <h3 class="font-sans font-bold text-[10px] uppercase tracking-widest text-slate-400 mb-2">Purpose</h3>
            <p class="text-sm font-medium italic text-slate-600">To demonstrate the three main functions of a river: erosion (carving), transportation (carrying), and sedimentation (depositing).</p>
            <h3 class="font-sans font-bold text-[10px] uppercase tracking-widest text-slate-400 mt-4 mb-2">Materials</h3>
            <ul class="text-sm font-medium italic text-slate-600 list-disc ml-5">
                <li><strong>Sand Tray:</strong> A large tray with a mound of sand sloped at one end.</li>
                <li><strong>Water Pitcher:</strong> Small, with a steady-pouring spout.</li>
                <li><strong>Blue Food Coloring:</strong> (Optional) to make the water more visible.</li>
                <li><strong>Bucket:</strong> To catch overflow.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2 class="font-sans font-bold text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-amber-600 mb-8 border-b pb-2 italic">Presentation</h2>

            <div class="action">Gather children around the sand tray. Smooth the sand to represent a mountain slope.</div>
            <div class="dialogue">"We know the water falls on the mountains. Now we will see what the water does as it travels down."</div>

            <div class="action">Pour water slowly but steadily at the top of the slope.</div>
            <div class="dialogue">"Watch the sand. See how the water is digging a path? It is cutting into the earth. We call this 'Carving'."</div>

            <div class="illustrate">
                <svg width="400" height="200" viewBox="0 0 400 200" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
                    <!-- Sloped Sand -->
                    <path d="M50 50 L150 150 L350 150" stroke="#94A3B8" stroke-width="2" style="stroke-dasharray: 4 2;"/>
                    <!-- Pitcher Skeleton -->
                    <path d="M40 20 L70 20 L60 50 L30 50 Z" stroke="#64748B" fill="#F1F5F9"/>
                    <!-- Water Stream -->
                    <path d="M65 35 Q80 80 120 120" stroke="#3B82F6" stroke-width="3"/>
                    <!-- The "V" Carve -->
                    <path d="M100 100 L115 125 L130 100" stroke="#1E293B" stroke-width="1"/>
                    <text x="140" y="110" font-family="Inter" font-size="10" fill="#1E293B" font-weight="bold">CARVING (Erosion)</text>
                </svg>
                <div class="illustrate-label">Fig 4.1: Water carving a V-shaped valley in the sand</div>
            </div>

            <div class="action">Point to the water in the channel. It should be murky with sand.</div>
            <div class="dialogue">"The water is not clear anymore. It is full of little pieces of earth. The river is acting like a truck, taking the sand from the mountain and 'Carrying' it along."</div>

            <div class="action">Observe the water as it reaches the flat bottom of the tray and slows down.</div>
            <div class="dialogue">"As the land gets flat, the water moves slower. It can't hold the heavy sand anymore. Watch it drop the sand right here. This is called 'Depositing'."</div>

            <div class="illustrate">
                <svg width="400" height="150" viewBox="0 0 400 150" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
                    <!-- River mouth -->
                    <path d="M50 75 L150 75 Q200 75 250 120 M150 75 Q200 75 250 30" stroke="#3B82F6" stroke-width="4"/>
                    <!-- Fan/Delta deposit -->
                    <path d="M180 75 L280 40 Q320 75 280 110 Z" fill="#E2E8F0" stroke="#94A3B8" stroke-dasharray="2 2"/>
                    <text x="280" y="130" font-family="Inter" font-size="10" fill="#64748B" font-weight="bold">DEPOSITING (Delta)</text>
                </svg>
                <div class="illustrate-label">Fig 4.2: The formation of a Delta or Alluvial Fan</div>
            </div>

            <div class="aside-box text-sm italic text-amber-900 leading-relaxed">
                "Guide Tip: This lesson provides the 'Why' behind the shape of our 3D model. The mountains are carved away (eroded) while the plains are built up (deposited). This is the great cosmic cycle of the Work of Water."
            </div>
        </section>

        <footer class="mt-20 pt-8 border-t text-[10px] font-sans text-slate-300 uppercase tracking-widest text-center">
            Elim Lee // Semester 4 Sprint // AMI Elementary
        </footer>
    </article>
    <script>
        lucide.createIcons();
    </script>
</body>
</html>
